genresAdvancedInfo.name: orebro indie
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Örebro indie is a subgenre of indie rock that originated in the Swedish city of Örebro. It is characterized by its lo-fi sound, DIY ethos, and introspective lyrics. Örebro indie bands often incorporate elements of folk, punk, and post-punk into their music, and lyrics often touch on themes of alienation, loneliness, and social commentary. The genre is known for its raw, authentic sound and its commitment to independent, underground music.
